reviews.review_text: listen to this show this show is so awesome, listen to it if you wanna hear some inspired dead. big boss man is the highlight for me. all the boys are on fire and this miller remaster is spectacular
YUMMY. Exellent from start to finish. Great C Miller sound.

Everything cannot be a five! Every show cannot be a five, no matter how well played (in my opinion). Especially one with Far From Me, Mexicali, Bucket, Looks Like Rain (in the 2nd set no less!), and Throwing/Not Fade. 

The opening was great, but it went downhill from there in my opinion.

Very well played from top to bottom... This is an excellent show. I, for one, care less about set lists (since I can appreciate every song the band does for one reason or another) than I do about excellent playing and performance.  This one smokes all the way through, especially the second set.  Even if you don't like it on paper, it is definitely worth a listen. It reminds me of 4/8/89 @ Riverfront, which also doesn't look great set list-wise, but is a great recording of the boys on fire. Thanks Charlie for all the aural pleasure.

Won't you tell everybody you meet.... I was at this show and had a great time.  On "tape" 20 plus years later, it has its hights and lows.  I will say, that at the time, I was particulary moved by candyman, and resolved to myself that I would, in fact, tell everyone I met that the candyman was in town.   The spell wore off by the time I exited, however, and I didnt follow through.  You decide if he was wise....
Jerry's Feeling Better But still a standard spin, No Highlights
